      "blockType": "header",
      "text": "[QID_SEC_012] 2.1 REQUIREMENTS AND CONTROLS",
      "qids": [
        "[QID_SEC_012]"
      ],
      "tocEntries": null,
      "confidence": 0.95
    },
    {
      "id": "block_11",
      "page": 3,
      "bbox": [
        0.12745098039215685,
        0.18592171717171718,
        0.8584802166309232,
        0.2487247544105607
      ],
      "blockType": "text",
      "text": "Requirements are statements of security and privacy objectives that a system must achieve. Controls are the safeguards or countermeasures employed within a system to satisfy those requirements. The relationship between requirements and controls is fundamental to understanding how security and privacy objectives are translated into actionable technical and operational measures.",
      "qids": null,
      "tocEntries": null,
      "confidence": 0.95
    },
    {
      "id": "block_12",
      "page": 3,
      "bbox": [
        0.12745098039215685,
        0.26517677307128906,
        0.6650326298732384,
        0.29291667360247986
      ],
      "blockType": "header",
      "text": "[QID_SEC_013] 2.2 CONTROL STRUCTURE AND ORGANIZATION",
      "qids": [
        "[QID_SEC_013]"
      ],
      "tocEntries": null,
      "confidence": 0.95
    },
    {
      "id": "block_13",
      "page": 3,
      "bbox": [
        0.12745098039215685,
        0.30082070707070707,
        0.8394279729307087,
        0.34847220989188765
      ],
      "blockType": "text",
      "text": "Controls in this publication are organized into twenty control families. Each family contains controls related to the security or privacy functionality of the family. The control families are aligned with the seventeen security-related areas in FIPS 200 and the privacy areas from OMB Circular A-130.",
      "qids": null,
      "tocEntries": null,
      "confidence": 0.95
    }
